The architecture is built to support 10,000+ concurrent users efficiently.
Route 53 and CloudFront help users reach the app faster with global content delivery.
Application Load Balancer (ALB) distributes incoming traffic across multiple servers.
AWS WAF protects the application from common web attacks and threats.
EC2 instances run in private subnets for security and form the main application layer.
An Auto Scaling Group automatically adds or removes EC2 servers based on traffic load.
ElastiCache (Redis) speeds up the application by caching frequently used data.
RDS/Aurora stores the main application data reliably with multi-AZ support.
Security Groups and NACLs control and filter traffic for each layer to ensure safety.
CloudWatch monitors system health, logs, performance, and sends alerts when needed.
